{"questionId": "2c8bbd7c-40a9-4e05-bc74-0279c5b08fcc_22", "correctAnswer": "D", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Use the factored form", "content": "Since the parabola has roots $9$ and $-2$, $f(x)=a(x-9)(x-(-2))$ for integer $a>1$."}, {"title": "Expand to find $a+b$", "content": "Expanding gives $f(x)=ax^2-a(9+(-2))x+a(9)(-2)$, so $b=-a(7)$ and $$a+b=a(1-(7))=-6a.$$"}, {"title": "Pick a valid $a$", "content": "With $a=2$ (integer $>1$), $a+b=-6\\cdot2=-12$. The answer is <strong>D</strong>.", "desmosExpressions": ["y = a(x-9)(x+2)", "(9, 0)", "(-2, 0)"]}]}